Netcare 911 responding to a crash in Hillcrest.Photo: supplied Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories ON Monday evening Netcare 911 paramedics responded to what was reported as a pedestrian crash along Shongweni Road in Hillcrest. According to paramedics an off-duty security officer was riding his bicycle home when he was hit by a vehicle. Chris Botha media liaison officer - Netcare 911 said: The Netcare 911 rescue officer found that the man had sustained moderate injuries. He was treated at the scene before medics transported him to a government hospital. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.